22
00:02:42,280 --> 00:02:43,880
So, in your eyes, human lives

23
00:02:44,310 --> 00:02:46,110
are no more than sweet potatoes?

24
00:02:46,310 --> 00:02:47,690
You really are absurd.

25
00:02:47,800 --> 00:02:48,590
They're just a bunch of

26
00:02:48,590 --> 00:02:50,910
fictional characters I created myself.

27
00:02:51,430 --> 00:02:52,630
How much more precious

28
00:02:52,630 --> 00:02:54,079
can their lives be
than this sweet potato...

29
00:02:54,079 --> 00:02:55,800
Even if they're just fictional characters,

30
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:57,650
you created them yourself.

31
00:02:57,750 --> 00:02:59,190
Didn't you invest your emotions

32
00:02:59,190 --> 00:03:00,560
and effort?

33
00:03:02,710 --> 00:03:04,030
On a screen,

34
00:03:04,360 --> 00:03:05,590
they're nothing more than

35
00:03:05,590 --> 00:03:08,320
lines of code—easily edited
and deleted at will.

36
00:03:09,240 --> 00:03:10,660
Today I kill one emperor,

37
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:12,520
and tomorrow I can write 100,

38
00:03:12,520 --> 00:03:13,310
1,000,

39
00:03:13,310 --> 00:03:14,240
or 10,000.

40
00:03:15,150 --> 00:03:16,210
Song Xiaoyu,

41
00:03:16,590 --> 00:03:19,190
you're the one who's
never been clear-headed.

42
00:03:19,400 --> 00:03:20,840
How are the people in this world

43
00:03:20,840 --> 00:03:21,680
